{{Infobox person | name = Gustavo Gaviria Angel | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = August 12, 1948 | birth_place = [[Bogota, Colombia]] | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = [[Colombia]] | spouse = Margareth Halaby | children = Laura Gaviria Halaby, Alejandro Gaviria Halaby | occupation = [[Entrepreneur]], | years_active = 48 | known_for = [[Expo 2010]], [[Expo 2016]], Ambassador on special Mission, Industrias Aliadas, Coffeecol | notable_works = Independent panel review of the World Bank Group Department of Institutional Integrity<ref name="gaviria-wb1">{{cite web |title=Independent Panel Review - World Bank Group - Department of Institutional Integrity |author= |url=http://siteresources.worldbank.org/NEWS/Resources/Volcker_Report_Sept._12,_for_website_FINAL.pdf |publisher=[[World Bank Group]] |date=June 28, 2016 |accessdate= }}</ref><ref name="gaviria-wb2">{{cite web |title=World Bank President Robert B. Zoellick Welcomes Volcker Panel Review of the World Bank's Institutional Integrity Department |author= |url=http://www.worldbank.org/en/news/press-release/2007/09/13/world-bank-president-robert-zoellick-welcomes-volcker-panel-review-world-bank-institutional-integrity-department |publisher=[[World Bank Group]] |date=September 13, 2007 |accessdate= }}</ref> }}
'''Gustavo Gaviria Angel''' (born August 12, 1948; [[Bogota, Colombia]]) is a Colombian coffee entrepreneur, founder and President of Industrias Aliadas, Coffeecol, Aurora and Chairman of Vision de Valores S.A. He is best known for his contribution as special ambassador of Colombia to the Milan [[Expo 2010]]<ref name="gaviria-expo2010-1"/> and the Shangai [[Expo 2015]].<ref name="gaviria-expo2015-1"/>
==Personal life== Gaviria studied [[industrial engineering]] from the [[University of Los Andes (Colombia)]]. He holds a [[Postgraduate education|postgraduate degree]] in [[management]] from [[University of La Sabana]] also known as Inalde.
==Career== Gaviria serves as an adviser of the [[International Finance Corporation]].
===Expo leadership=== Gaviria served as [[Ambassador]] of Colombia in special mission and general commissioner to [[Expo 2010]], known officially as Expo 2010 Shanghai China.<ref name="gaviria-expo2010-1">{{cite web |title=Colombia estará presente en Expo Shanghai 2010 |author= |url=http://www.semana.com/economia/articulo/colombia-estara-presente-expo-shanghai-2010/111121-3 |publisher=[[Semana]] |date=December 17, 2009 |accessdate= }}</ref><ref name="gaviria-expo2010-2">{{cite web |title=Expo Shanghai: A Golden Opportunity |author= |url=http://www.cancilleria.gov.co/sites/default/files/Expo%20Shanghai%20GUSTAVO%20GAVIRIA.pdf |publisher= |date= |accessdate= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title="Hay que descubrir Colombia a través de su corazón" |author= |url=http://spanish.china.org.cn/international/txt/2010-06/11/content_20236907_3.htm |publisher=spanish.china.org.cn |date=June 11, 2010 |accessdate= }}</ref>
Gaviria was member of Board of Directors of the Sustainable Food Pavilion at [[Expo 2015]], a Universal Exposition hosted by [[Milan, Italy]].<ref name="gaviria-expo2015-1">{{cite web |title=Interview: Dr. Gustavo Gaviria Angel, Member of the Board of Directors, Sustainable Food Pavilion |author=Ana Carcani Rold |url= |publisher=[[The Diplomatic Courier]] |date=May 9, 2013 |accessdate= }}</ref> In this capacity, he was responsible for introducing Colombia to the 3 million visitors of this event.
