'''Thomas Threader Garland''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|MBE|size=85%}} (7 February 1877 &ndash; 7 July 1964) was a New Zealand businessman, broadcaster, Methodist lay preacher and choirmaster. He was born in [[London]], England, on 7 February 1877.<ref name="DNZB Garland">{{DNZB|title=Thomas Threader Garland|first= Patrick|last= Day|id=4g6|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

In the [[1951 Birthday Honours (New Zealand)|1951 King's Birthday Honours]], Garland was appointed a [[Order of the British Empire|Member of the Order of the British Empire]] for services to the community, especially as a conductor of children's choirs.<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=39245 |date=7 June 1951 |page=3100 |supp=y }}</ref>

